Description: Provides a unified input-output interface for reading and writing
    tractograms — collections of 3-D polylines (streamlines) reconstructed by
    fibre-tracking algorithms applied to diffusion MRI data. Supported formats
    include VTK (.vtk), VTP (.vtp), medInria FDS (.fds), MRtrix TCK/TSF
    (.tck/.tsf), and TrackVis TRK (.trk), with additional formats accessible
    via the 'DIPY' Python library (reticulate). Tractograms are represented
    in R as lightweight S3 objects: a single tract is a numeric matrix
    (class 'streamline') and a collection of tracts is a list of such matrices
    (class 'bundle'). VTK support is provided at compile time by the 'rvtk'
    package, which supplies pre-compiled VTK libraries and headers so that no
    manual VTK installation is required on most platforms.
